<http://www.spektrix.com/improvcentrevancouver/event/57401ANHTKSRPPTMGTRKPHLCBHVSMPJSK>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Improv 102: the Funner-Damentals!";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Improv 102</h1><h2>The Funner-damentals!</h2><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">LOCATION UPDATE:</span><span><br/></span> July 25 & 26 Class will be held down the street at Carousel Theatre (1411 Cartwright St)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Day & Time:</span> Select Saturdays & Sundays at<span><br/></span>11:00am – 3:00pm (8 hours)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Age: </span>19+<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Level Required: </span>Improv 101<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Cost: </span>$195<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>This course builds on the basics of story from Improv 101 and uses it to create short scenes with a focus on characters and settings. We want to explore what creates a strong narrative while learning tips and tricks of what makes scenes more successful and rewarding for both the improviser and the audience.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>REFUND POLICY:<span><br/></span>No refunds. Day one and two of training must be attended consecutively in the booked weekend to ensure a trusting and collaborative experience for all students. Completion of course and eligibility for class advancement requires full attendance.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>LOCK OUT POLICY:<span><br/></span>Doors will lock 15 minutes after the class begins. Late comers will not be permitted.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>WAITLIST:<span><br/></span>If a class is sold out for a date you're hoping to attend, you can write in to <span class=\"BoldText\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"mailto:boxoffice@theimprovcentre.ca\">boxoffice@theimprovcentre.ca</a></span> to be added to a waitlist. While TIC can't guarantee you'll get a spot, we'll reach out if we can fit you in the class.
""";
